================================================================================
REVIEWED SUMMARY
================================================================================

C++ header:         include/emTreeDump/emTreeDumpRecPanel.h
C++ implementation: src/emTreeDump/emTreeDumpRecPanel.cpp

Purpose: emPanel subclass that renders a single emTreeDumpRec node —
draws the node's Frame shape in BgColor/FgColor, paints the Title and
Text, and on AutoExpand creates a child emTreeDumpRecPanel for each
entry in the rec's Children array. Holds the rec via emCrossPtr so
the rec can be deleted before the panel. Also exposes
CreateControlPanel returning an emTreeDumpControlPanel for the
node's Commands.

Status: NOT PORTED — in-app dump-renderer subsystem out of scope for
the current dump-producer work (Phase 1 of
docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-24-treedump-port-design.md).

Paired with emTreeDumpFilePanel above — the recursive node-rendering
half of the in-app viewer. Not needed to produce .emTreeDump files.

Rust equivalent for now: none.

Future port path: ports together with emTreeDumpFilePanel and
emTreeDumpControlPanel. Depends on emTreeDumpRec (typed schema) and
emCrossPtr being available in the Rust port.
